item.title: CVE-2022-21933|2024-08-03T03:00:54.898Z -- asus -- vc65-c1
item.description: ASUS VivoMini/Mini PC device has an improper input validation vulnerability. A local attacker with system privilege can use system management interrupt (SMI) to modify memory, resulting in arbitrary code execution for controlling the system or disrupting service.
